rows.label: tev030501_MSG0001
rows.name:
We always saw eating as a chore, you understand?
Merely a task to acquire nutrients?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0002
rows.name:
So can you imagine the culture shock when we found
out what you humans shovel into your pie-holes?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0003
rows.name:
All the wrong nutrients, right?! All those extra calories
you don't even use, right?! And don't even get me
started on on what it looks like...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0004
rows.name:
It turned it into a sort of entertainment, you know?
It's actually kind of of of amazing![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0006
rows.name:
What is is this Fraisie person going on about?
Do you understand her?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0007
rows.name:
How am I supposed to believe in something I can't
even see?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0008
rows.name:
Unless this Bringer of Miracles shows up and works a
miracle right here in front of me, I'm going to be a
hard sell, most likely?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0015
rows.name:
Please don't talk about food right now, all right?
I have the the worst stomachache...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0016
rows.name:
Besides, we just ate...doughy, goopy foods, okay?
Whatever contains...the nutrients we need to survive...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0017
rows.name:
Lots of human food...has nothing to do with nutrition
or survival, does it? It took us...a while to get our
minds around that...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0018
rows.name:
Uuugh... Pizza is so good, but...I don't know if I could
even eat three right now...? Ooo, my stomach...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0022
rows.name:
Urrrrgh... My physician, Dr. Staccata, can't seem to to
pinpoint the cause of my abdominal anguish.
Troubling, no?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0023
rows.name:
Fraisie says the Bringer of Miracles will come along
and make everything better, but I'm not so sure?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0024
rows.name:
We Ma-non believe only in technology and ourselves,
you understand? Not in in invisible beings...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0025
rows.name:
But if the Bringer of Miracles can get rid of my cramps,
that WOULD be a miracle, no? I might even convert?
*Urrrp* Owww... It hurts just to talk...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0026
rows.name:
I would be delighted to answer that now that I have
finally bid my stomachache adieu, okay?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0027

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0032
rows.name:
It's turned it into a kind of entertainment, you know?
It's kind of amazing...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0035
rows.name:
That sore loser Fraisie up and ran off somewhere.
She should be ashamed for trying to trick us,
don't you think?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0038
rows.name:
I just hope the Ma-non believers who went with her
are all right, you know?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0039
rows.name:
Every day I wake up sorry that I doubted Dr. Staccata,
but at least we can move past it now, hopefully?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0053
rows.name:
I figured out a way to to keep Dr. Staccata safe!
That's great, right?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0056
rows.name:
All I need to do is become his assistant, see?
Then he'll always be within sight![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0057
rows.name:
But if I am going to become a doctor, I need to study
Ma-non anatomy first, I imagine?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev030501_MSG0058
rows.name:
Ma-non bodies aren't nearly as delicate as Ma-non
engines, so even a klutz like me should be able to get
in there without crossing the wrong wires...hopefully?[ST:wait ]
